      "title": "The Letter in the Rain",
      "zhTitle": "雨中的信",
      "en": "Ethan Parker hated rainy days.\n\nRain made the streets gray.\nIt made the windows cold.\n\nAnd worst of all—\n\nRain always made the power go out in his apartment building.\n\n“Again?” Ethan sighed.\n\nThe lights flickered.\n\nThen everything became dark.\n\nHis grandmother lit a candle.\n\n“There,” she said warmly.\n\n“That’s better.”\n\nEthan sat near the window.\n\nOutside, rain hit the glass softly.\n\nDrip. Drip. Drip.\n\nHis grandmother smiled.\n\n“You always look so serious when it rains.”\n\n“I’m bored,” Ethan replied.\n\n“You say that every storm,” she laughed.\n\nEthan crossed his arms.\n\n“There’s nothing exciting here.”\n\nHis grandmother looked at him carefully.\n\n“Are you sure about that?”\n\nBefore Ethan could answer—\n\nKnock. Knock. Knock.\n\nSomeone was at the door.\n\n“At this hour?” Ethan asked.\n\nIt was almost midnight.\n\nHis grandmother stood slowly.\n\n“I’ll get it.”\n\nWhen she opened the door—\n\nNobody was there.\n\nOnly rain.\n\nAnd a black envelope.\n\nIt rested quietly on the floor.\n\nEthan blinked.\n\n“That’s weird.”\n\nHis grandmother picked it up carefully.\n\nThe envelope looked old.\n\nVery old.\n\nIt had a silver symbol on the front.\n\nA tower.\n\nAnd around the tower—\n\nTiny glowing stars.\n\nEthan stood up.\n\n“Who sent that?”\n\nHis grandmother did not answer immediately.\n\nInstead, she looked at the envelope silently.\n\nAlmost nervously.\n\n“Grandma?”\n\nShe handed it to him.\n\n“It has your name.”\n\nEthan looked down.\n\nWritten in silver ink were the words:\n\n✉️\n\nTo Ethan Parker\nRoom 7, Willow Street Apartments\nFor Immediate Delivery\n\nEthan frowned.\n\n“No stamp?”\n\n“No address from the sender?”\n\nThen something strange happened.\n\nThe silver letters began to glow.\n\nEthan almost dropped the envelope.\n\n“What is this?!”\n\n“Open it,” his grandmother said softly.\n\nEthan carefully broke the seal.\n\nInside was a thick paper letter.\n\nThe paper smelled like old books and rain.\n\nHe unfolded it slowly.\n\n✉️\n\nDear Ethan Parker,\n\nYou have been accepted into\nClock Tower Magic School.\n\nClasses begin in seven days.\n\nA train ticket is enclosed.\n\nDo not be late.\n\nThe tower bell rings only once.\n\nEthan stared at the letter.\n\nThen he laughed.\n\n“Okay… very funny.”\n\nBut his grandmother was not laughing.\n\nShe looked pale.\n\n“You need to go,” she whispered.\n\nEthan stopped smiling.\n\n“What?”\n\n“The school is real.”\n\nLightning flashed outside.\n\nBOOM.\n\nThunder shook the room.\n\nEthan looked at his grandmother.\n\n“You’re joking…”\n\nShe slowly sat down.\n\n“I hoped the letter would never come.”\n\n“What are you talking about?” Ethan asked.\n\nHis grandmother looked at the candle flame.\n\nThen she spoke quietly.\n\n“Your parents studied at Clock Tower Magic School.”\n\nEthan froze.\n\n“What?”\n\n“They were magic users.”\n\nThe room became silent.\n\nOnly the rain remained.\n\n“That’s impossible,” Ethan whispered.\n\nHis grandmother stood again.\n\nWithout saying a word—\n\nShe raised her hand.\n\nThe candle floated into the air.\n\nEthan’s eyes widened.\n\nThe candle slowly circled the room.\n\nThen gently returned to the table.\n\nEthan could not speak.\n\nHis heart raced wildly.\n\n“You’re… a magician?”\n\nHis grandmother smiled sadly.\n\n“In our world, we are called Keepers.”\n\nEthan looked at the letter again.\n\nThe silver tower symbol glowed softly.\n\n“This can’t be real…”\n\nBut deep inside—\n\nFor the first time in his life—\n\nEthan felt something strange.\n\nSomething exciting.\n\nSomething impossible.\n\nMagic.",
      "zh": "伊森・帕克討厭下雨天。\n\n雨會讓街道變灰。\n讓窗戶變冷。\n\n最糟的是——\n\n每次下大雨，他住的公寓總會停電。\n\n「又來了？」伊森嘆氣。\n\n燈閃了幾下。\n\n接著全部熄滅。\n\n奶奶點起一根蠟燭。\n\n「好了，」她溫柔地說。\n\n「這樣好多了。」\n\n伊森坐在窗邊。\n\n外面的雨輕輕打在玻璃上。\n\n滴答。滴答。滴答。\n\n奶奶笑著說：\n\n「你每次下雨都看起來很嚴肅。」\n\n「因為很無聊，」伊森回答。\n\n「你每次暴風雨都這樣說，」奶奶笑了。\n\n伊森抱起手。\n\n「這裡根本沒什麼有趣的事。」\n\n奶奶看著他。\n\n「你確定嗎？」\n\n就在這時——\n\n叩。叩。叩。\n\n有人敲門。\n\n「這麼晚？」伊森問。\n\n已經快午夜了。\n\n奶奶慢慢站起來。\n\n「我去看看。」\n\n當她打開門——\n\n外面沒有人。\n\n只有雨。\n\n還有一個黑色信封。\n\n靜靜躺在地上。\n\n伊森愣住。\n\n「好奇怪。」\n\n奶奶小心撿起信封。\n\n那封信看起來很古老。\n\n非常古老。\n\n正面有銀色圖案。\n\n一座高塔。\n\n周圍圍繞著發光的小星星。\n\n伊森站起來。\n\n「誰寄的？」\n\n奶奶沒有馬上回答。\n\n只是安靜看著信封。\n\n甚至有點緊張。\n\n「奶奶？」\n\n她把信遞給他。\n\n「上面寫你的名字。」\n\n伊森低頭。\n\n銀色字體寫著：\n\n✉️\n\n寄給\n伊森・帕克\n柳樹街公寓7號房\n立即送達\n\n伊森皺眉。\n\n「沒有郵票？」\n\n「也沒有寄件地址？」\n\n突然——\n\n銀色字開始發光。\n\n伊森差點把信丟掉。\n\n「這是什麼？！」\n\n「打開它，」奶奶輕聲說。\n\n伊森小心拆開封印。\n\n裡面是一張厚厚的紙。\n\n聞起來像舊書和雨水。\n\n他慢慢打開。\n\n✉️\n\n親愛的伊森・帕克：\n\n你已被錄取進入\n時鐘塔魔法學院。\n\n課程將於七天後開始。\n\n內附火車票。\n\n請勿遲到。\n\n鐘塔的鐘，只會響一次。\n\n伊森盯著信。\n\n然後笑了。\n\n「好喔……真好笑。」\n\n但奶奶沒有笑。\n\n她的臉色很蒼白。\n\n「你必須去，」她低聲說。\n\n伊森停止笑容。\n\n「什麼？」\n\n「那間學校是真的。」\n\n外面閃電劃過。\n\n轟隆！\n\n雷聲震動房間。\n\n伊森看著奶奶。\n\n「妳在開玩笑吧……」\n\n奶奶慢慢坐下。\n\n「我一直希望這封信不要來。」\n\n「妳到底在說什麼？」伊森問。\n\n奶奶看著蠟燭火光。\n\n然後輕聲說：\n\n「你的父母以前就在時鐘塔魔法學院讀書。」\n\n伊森愣住。\n\n「什麼？」\n\n「他們是魔法使用者。」\n\n房間安靜下來。\n\n只剩雨聲。\n\n「這不可能……」伊森低聲說。\n\n奶奶再次站起。\n\n一句話也沒說——\n\n她抬起手。\n\n蠟燭漂浮起來。\n\n伊森睜大眼睛。\n\n蠟燭慢慢繞著房間飛。\n\n然後輕輕回到桌上。\n\n伊森說不出話。\n\n心跳瘋狂加速。\n\n「妳……是魔法師？」\n\n奶奶露出淡淡微笑。\n\n「在我們的世界，我們被稱為『守護者』。」\n\n伊森再次看著那封信。\n\n銀色高塔圖案微微發光。\n\n「這不可能是真的……」\n\n但在他心裡深處——\n\n第一次——\n\n他感覺到某種東西。\n\n刺激。\n\n神秘。\n\n不可能。\n\n魔法。",
