      "title": "The Clock Tower School",
      "zhTitle": "時鐘塔魔法學院",
      "en": "The Midnight Train slowed as it climbed the mountain tracks.\n\nSteam covered the windows.\n\nThe giant tower grew larger and larger outside.\n\nEthan pressed his face against the glass.\n\nThe school was enormous.\n\nTall black towers stretched into the clouds.\n\nGolden clock faces glowed from every direction.\n\nBridges connected floating buildings in the air.\n\nBlue flames burned beside the pathways.\n\nAnd above everything—\n\nA massive clock ticked slowly at the top of the highest tower.\n\nTick…\n\nTick…\n\nTick…\n\nEthan whispered,\n\n“This place is unbelievable…”\n\nLucy grinned proudly.\n\n“Wait until you see the inside.”\n\nAdrian remained silent near the window.\n\nHis expression looked troubled.\n\nEthan noticed immediately.\n\n“You okay?”\n\nAdrian looked away.\n\n“…The Shadow Stalker should not have found the train.”\n\nLucy nodded nervously.\n\n“That never happens.”\n\nEthan touched the silver watch again.\n\n“You think it came because of this?”\n\nNeither of them answered.\n\nThat silence told Ethan enough.\n\nThe train finally stopped.\n\nSCREEEEEEE—\n\nA loud whistle echoed across the mountain.\n\nOutside, students hurried onto the station platform.\n\nCold night air rushed into the cabins.\n\n“Come on!” Lucy said excitedly.\n\n“We’re going to miss the arrival ceremony!”\n\nEthan grabbed his suitcase quickly.\n\nThe three of them stepped onto the platform.\n\nThe mountain air smelled like rain and smoke.\n\nHuge stone statues lined the pathway toward the school.\n\nEach statue held a glowing lantern.\n\nSome statues even moved slightly when students passed.\n\nEthan nearly jumped.\n\n“Did that statue just LOOK at me?”\n\nLucy laughed.\n\n“You get used to it.”\n\n“I don’t think I will.”\n\nFar above them, thunder rolled around the tower.\n\nThe giant clock rang once.\n\nDONGGGGG—\n\nThe sound shook the mountain itself.\n\nAll the students stopped walking immediately.\n\nThe air became silent.\n\nEven the wind disappeared.\n\nLucy whispered quietly,\n\n“That means the Headmaster is watching.”\n\nEthan looked up at the highest tower.\n\nFor one second—\n\nHe thought he saw someone standing near the giant clock.\n\nA tall figure in silver robes.\n\nWatching the new students below.\n\nThen lightning flashed—\n\nAnd the figure vanished.\n\n“Uh… was someone up there?”\n\nLucy looked confused.\n\n“Where?”\n\nBut Adrian’s face became serious again.\n\n“…Don’t stare at the tower too long.”\n\nEthan frowned.\n\n“Why?”\n\nAdrian looked away.\n\n“Because sometimes…”\n\n“The tower stares back.”\n\n“That is the least comforting thing I’ve ever heard.”\n\nLucy burst into laughter.\n\nThe students followed glowing lanterns toward the school gates.\n\nThe gates were enormous.\n\nBlack metal covered with silver symbols.\n\nAs Ethan walked closer—\n\nThe gates slowly opened by themselves.\n\nCREEEEEEAK—\n\nWarm golden light spilled outward.\n\nInside was a gigantic hall.\n\nFloating candles filled the air.\n\nLong tables stretched across the room.\n\nHundreds of students sat together in dark robes.\n\nAt the far end of the hall—\n\nA staircase floated in the air.\n\nMoving slowly.\n\nChanging direction by itself.\n\nEthan stared upward.\n\n“The stairs are floating?!”\n\nLucy smiled proudly.\n\n“Yep.”\n\n“They change every day.”\n\n“That sounds extremely dangerous.”\n\n“It is.”\n\nTeachers stood near the front of the hall.\n\nSome looked kind.\n\nSome looked terrifying.\n\nOne teacher had an eyepatch made of silver glass.\n\nAnother had glowing blue tattoos across both hands.\n\nAnd standing at the center—\n\nWas the Headmaster.\n\nHe wore long silver robes.\n\nWhite hair flowed down his shoulders.\n\nHis eyes glowed faintly gold.\n\nThe entire hall became silent when he stepped forward.\n\nHe looked ancient.\n\nPowerful.\n\nLike he could hear every heartbeat in the room.\n\n“Welcome,” he said calmly.\n\nHis voice echoed everywhere without being loud.\n\n“Welcome to Clock Tower Magic School.”\n\nThe floating candles brightened instantly.\n\n“Tonight, you begin your journey as Keepers.”\n\n“Some of you will learn courage.”\n\n“Some wisdom.”\n\n“Some sacrifice.”\n\nHis golden eyes slowly moved across the students.\n\nThen—\n\nFor the briefest moment—\n\nThey stopped on Ethan.\n\nThe silver watch suddenly ticked loudly.\n\nTick.\n\nThe Headmaster’s expression changed slightly.\n\nAlmost surprised.\n\nBut only for a second.\n\nThen he continued speaking normally.\n\n“You will soon be assigned to your tower houses.”\n\nLucy whispered excitedly,\n\n“This is the best part.”\n\nAt the center of the hall stood four giant banners.\n\nA silver wolf.\n\nA black raven.\n\nA golden lion.\n\nAnd a white serpent.\n\n“Each house trains different kinds of magic,” Lucy explained.\n\nEthan looked impressed.\n\n“That actually looks amazing.”\n\nSuddenly—\n\nBOOM.\n\nThe hall doors slammed shut by themselves.\n\nEvery candle flickered.\n\nCold wind rushed through the room.\n\nThe Headmaster stopped speaking immediately.\n\nTeachers stood up quickly.\n\nThe silver watch in Ethan’s pocket began ticking wildly.\n\nTickTickTickTickTick—\n\nAdrian whispered,\n\n“…No way.”\n\nA dark mark slowly appeared on the ceiling above the hall.\n\nSmoke spread outward like black veins.\n\nStudents screamed.\n\nThe floating candles turned blue.\n\nAnd from inside the darkness—\n\nTwo glowing purple eyes opened.\n\nWatching Ethan.",
