      "title": "The Hidden Library Beneath the Tower",
      "zhTitle": "高塔下的隱藏圖書館",
      "en": "The room stayed silent after the message appeared.\n\nCOME BELOW.\nALONE.\n\nThe glowing words slowly faded from the silver watch.\n\nTick…\n\nTick…\n\nTick…\n\nLucy crossed her arms immediately.\n\n“No.”\n\nEthan blinked.\n\n“…No?”\n\n“No,” Lucy repeated firmly.\n\n“You are absolutely NOT walking alone into the forbidden nightmare tower.”\n\nAdrian nodded once.\n\n“For once, I agree with her.”\n\nEthan looked toward the hidden staircase again.\n\nSilver light still glowed faintly below.\n\nThe Tower Keeper remained perfectly still beside it.\n\nWatching.\n\nWaiting.\n\nEthan took a slow breath.\n\n“But what if the tower has answers?”\n\nLucy pointed dramatically at the terrifying staircase.\n\n“And what if the answers kill you?”\n\n“That is also possible,” Adrian admitted.\n\n“Very comforting. Thank you.”\n\nThe silver watch suddenly became warm again.\n\nA soft light pointed downward.\n\nAlmost impatiently.\n\nEthan frowned.\n\n“It really wants me to go.”\n\nLucy looked nervous.\n\n“That sentence sounds worse every time you say it.”\n\nAdrian stepped closer to the staircase carefully.\n\nThe Tower Keeper immediately lowered its spear slightly.\n\nBlocking the path.\n\nAdrian stopped instantly.\n\n“…Interesting.”\n\n“What?”\n\n“It will only allow YOU to enter.”\n\nLucy groaned loudly.\n\n“Of course it will.”\n\nEthan stared into the staircase darkness.\n\nPart of him wanted to run away.\n\nFar away.\n\nBack home.\n\nBack to normal life.\n\nBut another part—\n\nA stronger part—\n\nNeeded to know the truth.\n\nAbout the tower.\n\nAbout the watch.\n\nAbout his father.\n\nEthan tightened his grip on the silver watch.\n\nThen he looked at his friends.\n\n“I’ll go.”\n\nLucy pointed at him in disbelief.\n\n“You have known magic for TWO DAYS.”\n\n“And now you want to explore haunted death stairs alone?!”\n\n“…When you say it like that, it sounds bad.”\n\n“Because IT IS BAD!”\n\nAdrian looked serious.\n\n“If you go below…”\n\n“Be careful what you trust.”\n\nEthan sighed.\n\n“Why does everyone in this school talk like cursed fortune cookies?”\n\nFor the first time that night—\n\nAdrian almost smiled.\n\nAlmost.\n\nEthan walked toward the hidden staircase slowly.\n\nThe Tower Keeper stepped aside immediately.\n\nBlue fire flickered across its armor.\n\nThe silver watch glowed brighter with every step Ethan took.\n\nBehind him, Lucy whispered nervously:\n\n“If he dies, I’m blaming you.”\n\n“I’m aware,” Adrian replied calmly.\n\nEthan stepped onto the staircase.\n\nThe moment he did—\n\nThe hidden doorway closed behind him.\n\nBOOM.\n\nDarkness swallowed the sound of his friends instantly.\n\nNow he was alone.\n\nOnly silver flames lit the path downward.\n\nStep after step.\n\nThe staircase spiraled deep beneath the school.\n\nThe air became colder.\n\nOlder.\n\nThe walls were covered with ancient symbols.\n\nSome moved slowly when Ethan looked away.\n\n“…Nope,” Ethan whispered.\n\n“I officially hate this place.”\n\nThe silver watch ticked louder.\n\nTick.\n\nTick.\n\nTick.\n\nThen suddenly—\n\nThe staircase ended.\n\nEthan stopped.\n\nHis eyes widened.\n\nA massive underground library stretched before him.\n\nThousands upon thousands of books filled enormous shelves.\n\nFloating lanterns drifted through the darkness.\n\nSilver chains hung from the ceiling.\n\nAncient clocks covered the walls.\n\nEvery clock showed a different time.\n\nTicking echoed everywhere.\n\nTick.\n\nTick.\n\nTick.\n\nAt the center of the library stood a giant tree made entirely of silver light.\n\nIts glowing branches reached toward the ceiling.\n\nBooks floated around it slowly.\n\nEthan whispered,\n\n“…What IS this place?”\n\nA voice answered from the darkness.\n\n“The Memory Library.”\n\nEthan spun around instantly.\n\nA figure stepped forward between the shelves.\n\nAn old woman wearing long gray robes.\n\nSilver symbols glowed across her sleeves.\n\nOne of her eyes was mechanical.\n\nClockwork gears moved inside it.\n\nThe woman studied Ethan carefully.\n\nThen she looked at the silver watch.\n\n“…So the tower chose you after all.”\n\nEthan stepped backward carefully.\n\n“Who are you?”\n\nThe old woman bowed slightly.\n\n“My name is Seraphine.”\n\n“I am the Keeper of Memories.”\n\nEthan blinked.\n\n“…That sounds extremely important.”\n\n“It is.”\n\nThe giant silver tree glowed brighter.\n\nSeraphine walked toward it slowly.\n\n“For hundreds of years, this library has protected the truth of the First Keepers.”\n\nEthan followed carefully.\n\n“And the tower brought me here because…?”\n\nSeraphine stopped beside the glowing tree.\n\nThen she turned toward Ethan.\n\n“Because your father once stood exactly where you stand now.”\n\nEthan froze.\n\nThe library suddenly felt much colder.\n\n“You knew my father?”\n\nSeraphine nodded slowly.\n\n“Yes.”\n\n“And if the tower has awakened for you…”\n\nHer mechanical eye glowed faintly.\n\n“…Then the darkness sealed beneath the school may also be awakening.”\n\nEthan’s stomach tightened.\n\n“…What darkness?”\n\nThe giant silver tree suddenly shook violently.\n\nBooks began flying through the air.\n\nThe clocks around the library started spinning backward.\n\nFAST.\n\nTickTickTickTickTick—\n\nSeraphine’s expression changed immediately.\n\n“No…”\n\nThe silver watch in Ethan’s hand flashed bright light.\n\nThen—\n\nA giant crack appeared across the library floor.\n\nDark smoke rose from below.\n\nPurple light glowed deep inside the darkness.\n\nAnd from somewhere far beneath the tower—\n\nSomething laughed.",
