      "en": "Three months later…\n\nSnow covered the mountains around Clock Tower School.\n\nWinter winds howled softly outside the castle windows.\n\nInside the school—\n\nEverything had changed.\n\nThe broken clocks were repaired.\n\nThe floating staircases moved normally again.\n\nThe dark cracks beneath the tower had disappeared.\n\nAnd for the first time in many years—\n\nThe school felt peaceful.\n\nMostly peaceful.\n\nLucy still ran through hallways while carrying far too many books.\n\n“ETHAN!”\n\nShe nearly crashed into him beside the west tower stairs.\n\n“You missed breakfast again!”\n\nEthan smiled tiredly.\n\n“I was studying.”\n\nLucy narrowed her eyes.\n\n“You were sleeping in the library.”\n\n“…Maybe.”\n\n“I KNEW IT.”\n\nBehind them, Adrian approached calmly with his usual serious expression.\n\n“You’re both too loud.”\n\nLucy pointed at him dramatically.\n\n“You secretly enjoy our chaos.”\n\n“I absolutely do not.”\n\nEthan laughed quietly.\n\nSome things never changed.\n\nBut other things had changed forever.\n\nThe silver Keeper symbol still glowed faintly on Ethan’s hand.\n\nMost students could not see it.\n\nBut Ethan could feel it constantly.\n\nA soft connection beneath the tower.\n\nFar below the school—\n\nThe prison still existed.\n\nAnd so did the Hollow King.\n\nWaiting.\n\nSleeping.\n\nWatching.\n\nSometimes Ethan could hear distant heartbeats at night.\n\nTHUMP.\n\nTHUMP.\n\nTHUMP.\n\nNot dangerous anymore.\n\nJust… there.\n\nA reminder.\n\nThe silver watch ticked softly in his pocket.\n\nTick.\n\nTick.\n\nTick.\n\nEthan pulled it out slowly.\n\nThe watch looked different now.\n\nThe old prison symbol had vanished.\n\nIn its place was a new symbol.\n\nA silver flame surrounded by a clock circle.\n\nThe symbol of the Free Keeper.\n\nSeraphine had explained it weeks ago.\n\n“The prison now obeys human will.”\n\n“No tower.”\n\n“No ancient magic.”\n\n“Only the Keeper’s choice.”\n\nEthan still was not sure how he felt about that.\n\nSome nights he felt brave.\n\nOther nights—\n\nTerrified.\n\nBecause now he understood something important.\n\nPower was dangerous.\n\nEven magical towers could become monsters.\n\nThat was why choices mattered.\n\nAnd why freedom mattered even more.\n\nSnow drifted softly outside the windows.\n\nStudents laughed somewhere down the hallway.\n\nLife continued.\n\nFor the first time since arriving at the school—\n\nEthan finally felt like he belonged there.\n\nThen suddenly—\n\nTickTickTick.\n\nThe silver watch glowed softly.\n\nEthan frowned.\n\n“…That’s new.”\n\nLucy leaned closer immediately.\n\n“What is it?”\n\nA tiny silver message appeared on the watch surface.\n\nTHE EAST TOWER HAS OPENED.\n\nAdrian stopped walking.\n\n“…That tower has been sealed for over a hundred years.”\n\nLucy blinked.\n\n“Oh no.”\n\nEthan stared at the glowing words.\n\nThen slowly smiled.\n\n“…Well.”\n\nHe adjusted his school robe.\n\n“Looks like the school is trying to kill us again.”\n\nLucy groaned dramatically.\n\n“I JUST survived one magical apocalypse!”\n\nAdrian sighed deeply.\n\n“…We’re going, aren’t we?”\n\nEthan grinned.\n\n“Definitely.”\n\nFar above them—\n\nOne of the giant Clock Tower bells rang softly through the snow.\n\nDONG…\n\nAnd somewhere deep inside the ancient school—\n\nAnother secret waited to awaken.",
      "zh": "三個月後——\n\n白雪覆蓋時鐘塔學院周圍山脈。\n\n冬季寒風輕輕吹過城堡窗外。\n\n而在學校裡——\n\n一切都改變了。\n\n破碎時鐘被修復。\n\n漂浮樓梯恢復正常。\n\n高塔底下黑暗裂縫消失。\n\n而且很多年來第一次——\n\n整間學校變得平靜。\n\n大部分時候算平靜。\n\n露西依然抱著一大堆書在走廊奔跑。\n\n「伊森！」\n\n她差點在西塔樓梯撞上伊森。\n\n「你又錯過早餐了！」\n\n伊森疲憊笑著。\n\n「我在讀書。」\n\n露西瞇起眼。\n\n「你是在圖書館睡覺。」\n\n「……可能吧。」\n\n「我就知道！」\n\n後方，亞德里安依舊帶著嚴肅表情走來。\n\n「你們太吵了。」\n\n露西誇張指著他。\n\n「你其實很喜歡我們的混亂。」\n\n「我完全沒有。」\n\n伊森輕聲笑了。\n\n有些事情永遠不會改變。\n\n但有些事情——\n\n已經永遠不同。\n\n銀色守護者印記依然微微發光。\n\n大部分學生看不見。\n\n但伊森一直感覺得到。\n\n那是一種與高塔底部相連的感覺。\n\n在學校深處——\n\n監獄依然存在。\n\n虛空之王也還存在。\n\n等待著。\n\n沉睡著。\n\n注視著。\n\n有時夜晚時，\n\n伊森仍會聽見遙遠心跳聲。\n\n咚。\n\n咚。\n\n咚。\n\n現在已經不再危險。\n\n只是……存在著。\n\n像提醒一樣。\n\n銀色懷錶在口袋裡輕輕滴答。\n\n滴答。\n\n滴答。\n\n滴答。\n\n伊森慢慢拿出懷錶。\n\n它現在不一樣了。\n\n原本的監獄符號已消失。\n\n取而代之——\n\n是一個新圖案。\n\n銀色火焰包圍時鐘圓環。\n\n自由守護者的象徵。\n\n幾週前瑟拉芬曾解釋過。\n\n「現在監獄服從人類意志。」\n\n「不再是高塔。」\n\n「不再是古老魔法。」\n\n「而是守護者自己的選擇。」\n\n伊森直到現在仍不確定自己的感受。\n\n有些夜晚，他覺得自己很勇敢。\n\n但有些夜晚——\n\n非常害怕。\n\n因為現在他終於明白一件事。\n\n力量是危險的。\n\n甚至連魔法高塔都可能變成怪物。\n\n所以選擇才重要。\n\n而自由，\n\n更加重要。\n\n雪靜靜飄落窗外。\n\n遠處傳來學生笑聲。\n\n生活仍在繼續。\n\n自從來到學校後——\n\n伊森第一次真正感覺自己屬於這裡。\n\n突然——\n\n滴答滴答。\n\n銀色懷錶微微發光。\n\n伊森皺眉。\n\n「……這倒是新狀況。」\n\n露西立刻湊近。\n\n「怎麼了？」\n\n懷錶表面浮現小小銀色文字。\n\n「東塔已開啟。」\n\n亞德里安瞬間停下腳步。\n\n「……那座塔封印超過一百年了。」\n\n露西眨眼。\n\n「喔不。」\n\n伊森盯著發光文字。\n\n接著慢慢笑了。\n\n「……好吧。」\n\n他整理校袍。\n\n「看來學校又想殺掉我們了。」\n\n露西誇張哀號。\n\n「我才剛從魔法世界末日活下來耶！」\n\n亞德里安深深嘆氣。\n\n「……我們還是會去，對吧？」\n\n伊森露出笑容。\n\n「當然。」\n\n而在高空之上——\n\n時鐘塔巨大鐘聲穿過雪夜輕輕響起。\n\n噹……\n\n而在古老學院深處——\n\n另一個秘密，\n\n正在等待甦醒。\n\nEND",
